The paper deals with the problem of constructing fault tolerant spanners, which is a fundamental problem in the field of distributed computing and graph theory. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve graph algorithms, combinatorial optimization, and probabilistic analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and linear programming, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
